cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
title: "vsk-session-item-recommendation: FOSS semantic-ID generative retrieval for session-based Godot asset recommendation"
abstract: >-
  A pure-PyTorch, FOSS (Apache-2.0 / MIT) session-based item recommender for user-generated Godot
  scene/assets. Items are encoded from multimodal content (scene/XMP text, image, mesh, audio, and a
  canonical body phenotype for humanoid assets) and quantized into discrete semantic IDs with Finite
  Scalar Quantization; a Transformer generates the next item's IDs. The design is allocentric and
  item-centric (i2i), giving cold-start / new-item churn robustness for a UGC catalog. This work
  migrates the recommender off the TensorFlow-based LibRecommender / PinSage baseline.
authors:
  - family-names: Lee
    given-names: "K. S. Ernest (iFire)"
    email: ernest.lee@chibifire.com
version: 0.1.0-dev.1
date-released: "2026-07-12"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/V-Sekai-fire/vsk-session-item-recommendation-01"
keywords:
  - recommender-systems
  - generative-retrieval
  - semantic-ids
  - finite-scalar-quantization
  - session-based-recommendation
  - multimodal
  - cold-start
  - godot
  - v-sekai

